51/***** radeon AUX functions *****/
52
53/* Atom needs data in little endian format so swap as appropriate when copying
54 * data to or from atom. Note that atom operates on dw units.
55 *
56 * Use to_le=true when sending data to atom and provide at least
57 * ALIGN(num_bytes,4) bytes in the dst buffer.
58 *
59 * Use to_le=false when receiving data from atom and provide ALIGN(num_bytes,4)
60 * byes in the src buffer.
61 */
62void radeon_atom_copy_swap(u8 *dst, u8 *src, u8 num_bytes, bool to_le)
63{
64#ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN
65 u32 src_tmp[5], dst_tmp[5];
66 int i;
67 u8 align_num_bytes = ALIGN(num_bytes, 4);
68
69 if (to_le) {
70 memcpy(src_tmp, src, num_bytes);
71 for (i = 0; i < align_num_bytes / 4; i++)
72 dst_tmp[i] = cpu_to_le32(src_tmp[i]);
73 memcpy(dst, dst_tmp, align_num_bytes);
74 } else {
75 memcpy(src_tmp, src, align_num_bytes);
76 for (i = 0; i < align_num_bytes / 4; i++)
77 dst_tmp[i] = le32_to_cpu(src_tmp[i]);
78 memcpy(dst, dst_tmp, num_bytes);
79 }
80#else
81 memcpy(dst, src, num_bytes);
82#endif
83}

85union aux_channel_transaction {
86 PROCESS_AUX_CHANNEL_TRANSACTION_PS_ALLOCATION v1;
87 PROCESS_AUX_CHANNEL_TRANSACTION_PARAMETERS_V2 v2;
88};
89
90static int radeon_process_aux_ch(struct radeon_i2c_chan *chan,
91 u8 *send, int send_bytes,
92 u8 *recv, int recv_size,
93 u8 delay, u8 *ack)
94{
95 struct drm_device *dev = chan->dev;
96 struct radeon_device *rdev = dev->dev_private;
97 union aux_channel_transaction args;
98 int index = GetIndexIntoMasterTable(COMMAND, ProcessAuxChannelTransaction);
99 unsigned char *base;
100 int recv_bytes;
101 int r = 0;
102
103 memset(&args, 0, sizeof(args));
104
105 mutex_lock(&chan->mutex);
106 mutex_lock(&rdev->mode_info.atom_context->scratch_mutex);
107
108 base = (unsigned char *)(rdev->mode_info.atom_context->scratch + 1);
109
110 radeon_atom_copy_swap(base, send, send_bytes, true);
111
112 args.v1.lpAuxRequest = cpu_to_le16((u16)(0 + 4));
113 args.v1.lpDataOut = cpu_to_le16((u16)(16 + 4));
114 args.v1.ucDataOutLen = 0;
115 args.v1.ucChannelID = chan->rec.i2c_id;
116 args.v1.ucDelay = delay / 10;
117 if (ASIC_IS_DCE4(rdev))
118 args.v2.ucHPD_ID = chan->rec.hpd;
119
120 atom_execute_table_scratch_unlocked(rdev->mode_info.atom_context, index, (uint32_t *)&args);
121
122 *ack = args.v1.ucReplyStatus;
123
124 /* timeout */
125 if (args.v1.ucReplyStatus == 1) {
126 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("dp_aux_ch timeout\n");
127 r = -ETIMEDOUT;
128 goto done;
129 }
130
131 /* flags not zero */
132 if (args.v1.ucReplyStatus == 2) {
133 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("dp_aux_ch flags not zero\n");
134 r = -EIO;
135 goto done;
136 }
137
138 /* error */
139 if (args.v1.ucReplyStatus == 3) {
140 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("dp_aux_ch error\n");
141 r = -EIO;
142 goto done;
143 }
144
145 recv_bytes = args.v1.ucDataOutLen;
146 if (recv_bytes > recv_size)
147 recv_bytes = recv_size;
148
149 if (recv && recv_size)
150 radeon_atom_copy_swap(recv, base + 16, recv_bytes, false);
151
152 r = recv_bytes;
153done:
154 mutex_unlock(&rdev->mode_info.atom_context->scratch_mutex);
155 mutex_unlock(&chan->mutex);
156
157 return r;
158}
159
160#define BARE_ADDRESS_SIZE 3
161#define HEADER_SIZE (BARE_ADDRESS_SIZE + 1)
162
163static ssize_t
164radeon_dp_aux_transfer_atom(struct drm_dp_aux *aux, struct drm_dp_aux_msg *msg)
165{
166 struct radeon_i2c_chan *chan =
167 container_of(aux, struct radeon_i2c_chan, aux);
168 int ret;
169 u8 tx_buf[20];
170 size_t tx_size;
171 u8 ack, delay = 0;
172
173 if (WARN_ON(msg->size > 16))
174 return -E2BIG;
175
176 tx_buf[0] = msg->address & 0xff;
177 tx_buf[1] = (msg->address >> 8) & 0xff;
178 tx_buf[2] = (msg->request << 4) |
179 ((msg->address >> 16) & 0xf);
180 tx_buf[3] = msg->size ? (msg->size - 1) : 0;
181
182 switch (msg->request & ~DP_AUX_I2C_MOT) {
183 case DP_AUX_NATIVE_WRITE:
184 case DP_AUX_I2C_WRITE:
185 case DP_AUX_I2C_WRITE_STATUS_UPDATE:
186 /* The atom implementation only supports writes with a max payload of
187 * 12 bytes since it uses 4 bits for the total count (header + payload)
188 * in the parameter space. The atom interface supports 16 byte
189 * payloads for reads. The hw itself supports up to 16 bytes of payload.
190 */
191 if (WARN_ON_ONCE(msg->size > 12))
192 return -E2BIG;
193 /* tx_size needs to be 4 even for bare address packets since the atom
194 * table needs the info in tx_buf[3].
195 */
196 tx_size = HEADER_SIZE + msg->size;
197 if (msg->size == 0)
198 tx_buf[3] |= BARE_ADDRESS_SIZE << 4;
199 else
200 tx_buf[3] |= tx_size << 4;
201 memcpy(tx_buf + HEADER_SIZE, msg->buffer, msg->size);
202 ret = radeon_process_aux_ch(chan,
203 tx_buf, tx_size, NULL, 0, delay, &ack);
204 if (ret >= 0)
205 /* Return payload size. */
206 ret = msg->size;
207 break;
208 case DP_AUX_NATIVE_READ:
209 case DP_AUX_I2C_READ:
210 /* tx_size needs to be 4 even for bare address packets since the atom
211 * table needs the info in tx_buf[3].
212 */
213 tx_size = HEADER_SIZE;
214 if (msg->size == 0)
215 tx_buf[3] |= BARE_ADDRESS_SIZE << 4;
216 else
217 tx_buf[3] |= tx_size << 4;
218 ret = radeon_process_aux_ch(chan,
219 tx_buf, tx_size, msg->buffer, msg->size, delay, &ack);
220 break;
221 default:
222 ret = -EINVAL;
223 break;
224 }
225
226 if (ret >= 0)
227 msg->reply = ack >> 4;
228
229 return ret;
230}

232void radeon_dp_aux_init(struct radeon_connector *radeon_connector)
233{
234 struct drm_device *dev = radeon_connector->base.dev;
235 struct radeon_device *rdev = dev->dev_private;
236 int ret;
237
238 radeon_connector->ddc_bus->rec.hpd = radeon_connector->hpd.hpd;
239 radeon_connector->ddc_bus->aux.dev = radeon_connector->base.kdev;
240 if (ASIC_IS_DCE5(rdev)) {
241 if (radeon_auxch)
242 radeon_connector->ddc_bus->aux.transfer = radeon_dp_aux_transfer_native;
243 else
244 radeon_connector->ddc_bus->aux.transfer = radeon_dp_aux_transfer_atom;
245 } else {
246 radeon_connector->ddc_bus->aux.transfer = radeon_dp_aux_transfer_atom;
247 }
248
249#ifdef __NetBSD__
250 /* XXX dervied from sysfs/i2c on linux. */
251 radeon_connector->ddc_bus->aux.name = "radeon_dp_aux";
252#endif
253
254 ret = drm_dp_aux_register(&radeon_connector->ddc_bus->aux);
255 if (!ret)
256 radeon_connector->ddc_bus->has_aux = true;
257
258 WARN(ret, "drm_dp_aux_register() failed with error %d\n", ret);
259}

261/***** general DP utility functions *****/

263#define DP_VOLTAGE_MAX DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_3
264#define DP_PRE_EMPHASIS_MAX DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_3
265
266static void dp_get_adjust_train(const u8 link_status[DP_LINK_STATUS_SIZE],
267 int lane_count,
268 u8 train_set[4])
269{
270 u8 v = 0;
271 u8 p = 0;
272 int lane;
273
274 for (lane = 0; lane < lane_count; lane++) {
275 u8 this_v = drm_dp_get_adjust_request_voltage(link_status, lane);
276 u8 this_p = drm_dp_get_adjust_request_pre_emphasis(link_status, lane);
277
278 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("requested signal parameters: lane %d voltage %s pre_emph %s\n",
279 lane,
280 voltage_names[this_v >> DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_SHIFT],
281 pre_emph_names[this_p >> DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPHASIS_SHIFT]);
282
283 if (this_v > v)
284 v = this_v;
285 if (this_p > p)
286 p = this_p;
287 }
288
289 if (v >= DP_VOLTAGE_MAX)
290 v |= DP_TRAIN_MAX_SWING_REACHED;
291
292 if (p >= DP_PRE_EMPHASIS_MAX)
293 p |= DP_TRAIN_MAX_PRE_EMPHASIS_REACHED;
294
295 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("using signal parameters: voltage %s pre_emph %s\n",
296 voltage_names[(v & DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_MASK) >> DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_SHIFT],
297 pre_emph_names[(p & DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPHASIS_MASK) >> DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPHASIS_SHIFT]);
298
299 for (lane = 0; lane < 4; lane++)
300 train_set[lane] = v | p;
301}

303/* convert bits per color to bits per pixel */
304/* get bpc from the EDID */
305static int convert_bpc_to_bpp(int bpc)
306{
307 if (bpc == 0)
308 return 24;
309 else
310 return bpc * 3;
311}

313/***** radeon specific DP functions *****/
314
315int radeon_dp_get_dp_link_config(struct drm_connector *connector,
316 const u8 dpcd[DP_DPCD_SIZE],
317 unsigned pix_clock,
318 unsigned *dp_lanes, unsigned *dp_rate)
319{
320 int bpp = convert_bpc_to_bpp(radeon_get_monitor_bpc(connector));
321 static const unsigned link_rates[3] = { 162000, 270000, 540000 };
322 unsigned max_link_rate = drm_dp_max_link_rate(dpcd);
323 unsigned max_lane_num = drm_dp_max_lane_count(dpcd);
324 unsigned lane_num, i, max_pix_clock;
325
326 if (radeon_connector_encoder_get_dp_bridge_encoder_id(connector) ==
327 ENCODER_OBJECT_ID_NUTMEG) {
328 for (lane_num = 1; lane_num <= max_lane_num; lane_num <<= 1) {
329 max_pix_clock = (lane_num * 270000 * 8) / bpp;
330 if (max_pix_clock >= pix_clock) {
331 *dp_lanes = lane_num;
332 *dp_rate = 270000;
333 return 0;
334 }
335 }
336 } else {
337 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(link_rates) && link_rates[i] <= max_link_rate; i++) {
338 for (lane_num = 1; lane_num <= max_lane_num; lane_num <<= 1) {
339 max_pix_clock = (lane_num * link_rates[i] * 8) / bpp;
340 if (max_pix_clock >= pix_clock) {
341 *dp_lanes = lane_num;
342 *dp_rate = link_rates[i];
343 return 0;
344 }
345 }
346 }
347 }
348
349 return -EINVAL;
350}
351
352static u8 radeon_dp_encoder_service(struct radeon_device *rdev,
353 int action, int dp_clock,
354 u8 ucconfig, u8 lane_num)
355{
356 DP_ENCODER_SERVICE_PARAMETERS args;
357 int index = GetIndexIntoMasterTable(COMMAND, DPEncoderService);
358
359 memset(&args, 0, sizeof(args));
360 args.ucLinkClock = dp_clock / 10;
361 args.ucConfig = ucconfig;
362 args.ucAction = action;
363 args.ucLaneNum = lane_num;
364 args.ucStatus = 0;
365
366 atom_execute_table(rdev->mode_info.atom_context, index, (uint32_t *)&args);
367 return args.ucStatus;
368}

370u8 radeon_dp_getsinktype(struct radeon_connector *radeon_connector)
371{
372 struct drm_device *dev = radeon_connector->base.dev;

379static void radeon_dp_probe_oui(struct radeon_connector *radeon_connector)
380{
381 struct radeon_connector_atom_dig *dig_connector = radeon_connector->con_priv;
382 u8 buf[3];
383
384 if (!(dig_connector->dpcd[DP_DOWN_STREAM_PORT_COUNT] & DP_OUI_SUPPORT))
385 return;
386
387 if (drm_dp_dpcd_read(&radeon_connector->ddc_bus->aux, DP_SINK_OUI, buf, 3) == 3)
388 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Sink OUI: %02hhx%02hhx%02hhx\n",
389 buf[0], buf[1], buf[2]);
390
391 if (drm_dp_dpcd_read(&radeon_connector->ddc_bus->aux, DP_BRANCH_OUI, buf, 3) == 3)
392 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Branch OUI: %02hhx%02hhx%02hhx\n",
393 buf[0], buf[1], buf[2]);
394}
395
396bool radeon_dp_getdpcd(struct radeon_connector *radeon_connector)
397{
398 struct radeon_connector_atom_dig *dig_connector = radeon_connector->con_priv;
399 u8 msg[DP_DPCD_SIZE];
400 int ret, i;
401
402 for (i = 0; i < 7; i++) {
403 ret = drm_dp_dpcd_read(&radeon_connector->ddc_bus->aux, DP_DPCD_REV, msg,
404 DP_DPCD_SIZE);
405 if (ret == DP_DPCD_SIZE) {
406 memcpy(dig_connector->dpcd, msg, DP_DPCD_SIZE);
407
408 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("DPCD: %*ph\n", (int)sizeof(dig_connector->dpcd),
409 dig_connector->dpcd);
410
411 radeon_dp_probe_oui(radeon_connector);
412
413 return true;
414 }
415 }
416 dig_connector->dpcd[0] = 0;
417 return false;
418}
419
420int radeon_dp_get_panel_mode(struct drm_encoder *encoder,
421 struct drm_connector *connector)
422{
423 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;
424 struct radeon_device *rdev = dev->dev_private;
425 struct radeon_connector *radeon_connector = to_radeon_connector(connector);
426 int panel_mode = DP_PANEL_MODE_EXTERNAL_DP_MODE;
427 u16 dp_bridge = radeon_connector_encoder_get_dp_bridge_encoder_id(connector);
428 u8 tmp;
429
430 if (!ASIC_IS_DCE4(rdev))
431 return panel_mode;
432
433 if (!radeon_connector->con_priv)
434 return panel_mode;
435
436 if (dp_bridge != ENCODER_OBJECT_ID_NONE) {
437 /* DP bridge chips */
438 if (drm_dp_dpcd_readb(&radeon_connector->ddc_bus->aux,
439 DP_EDP_CONFIGURATION_CAP, &tmp) == 1) {
440 if (tmp & 1)
441 panel_mode = DP_PANEL_MODE_INTERNAL_DP2_MODE;
442 else if ((dp_bridge == ENCODER_OBJECT_ID_NUTMEG) ||
443 (dp_bridge == ENCODER_OBJECT_ID_TRAVIS))
444 panel_mode = DP_PANEL_MODE_INTERNAL_DP1_MODE;
445 else
446 panel_mode = DP_PANEL_MODE_EXTERNAL_DP_MODE;
447 }
448 } else if (connector->connector_type == DRM_MODE_CONNECTOR_eDP) {
449 /* eDP */
450 if (drm_dp_dpcd_readb(&radeon_connector->ddc_bus->aux,
451 DP_EDP_CONFIGURATION_CAP, &tmp) == 1) {
452 if (tmp & 1)
453 panel_mode = DP_PANEL_MODE_INTERNAL_DP2_MODE;
454 }
455 }
456
457 return panel_mode;
458}
459
460void radeon_dp_set_link_config(struct drm_connector *connector,
461 const struct drm_display_mode *mode)
462{
463 struct radeon_connector *radeon_connector = to_radeon_connector(connector);
464 struct radeon_connector_atom_dig *dig_connector;
465 int ret;
466
467 if (!radeon_connector->con_priv)
468 return;
469 dig_connector = radeon_connector->con_priv;
470
471 if ((dig_connector->dp_sink_type == CONNECTOR_OBJECT_ID_DISPLAYPORT) ||
472 (dig_connector->dp_sink_type == CONNECTOR_OBJECT_ID_eDP)) {
473 ret = radeon_dp_get_dp_link_config(connector, dig_connector->dpcd,
474 mode->clock,
475 &dig_connector->dp_lane_count,
476 &dig_connector->dp_clock);
477 if (ret) {
478 dig_connector->dp_clock = 0;
479 dig_connector->dp_lane_count = 0;
480 }
481 }
482}
483
484int radeon_dp_mode_valid_helper(struct drm_connector *connector,
485 struct drm_display_mode *mode)
486{
487 struct radeon_connector *radeon_connector = to_radeon_connector(connector);
488 struct radeon_connector_atom_dig *dig_connector;
489 unsigned dp_clock, dp_lanes;
490 int ret;
491
492 if ((mode->clock > 340000) &&
493 (!radeon_connector_is_dp12_capable(connector)))
494 return MODE_CLOCK_HIGH;
495
496 if (!radeon_connector->con_priv)
497 return MODE_CLOCK_HIGH;
498 dig_connector = radeon_connector->con_priv;
499
500 ret = radeon_dp_get_dp_link_config(connector, dig_connector->dpcd,
501 mode->clock,
502 &dp_lanes,
503 &dp_clock);
504 if (ret)
505 return MODE_CLOCK_HIGH;
506
507 if ((dp_clock == 540000) &&
508 (!radeon_connector_is_dp12_capable(connector)))
509 return MODE_CLOCK_HIGH;
510
511 return MODE_OK;
512}
513
514bool radeon_dp_needs_link_train(struct radeon_connector *radeon_connector)
515{
516 u8 link_status[DP_LINK_STATUS_SIZE];
517 struct radeon_connector_atom_dig *dig = radeon_connector->con_priv;
518
519 if (drm_dp_dpcd_read_link_status(&radeon_connector->ddc_bus->aux, link_status)
520 <= 0)
521 return false;
522 if (drm_dp_channel_eq_ok(link_status, dig->dp_lane_count))
523 return false;
524 return true;
525}
526
527void radeon_dp_set_rx_power_state(struct drm_connector *connector,
528 u8 power_state)
529{
530 struct radeon_connector *radeon_connector = to_radeon_connector(connector);
531 struct radeon_connector_atom_dig *dig_connector;
532
533 if (!radeon_connector->con_priv)
534 return;
535
536 dig_connector = radeon_connector->con_priv;
537
538 /* power up/down the sink */
539 if (dig_connector->dpcd[0] >= 0x11) {
540 drm_dp_dpcd_writeb(&radeon_connector->ddc_bus->aux,
541 DP_SET_POWER, power_state);
542 usleep_range(1000, 2000);
543 }
544}

547struct radeon_dp_link_train_info {
548 struct radeon_device *rdev;
549 struct drm_encoder *encoder;
550 struct drm_connector *connector;
551 int enc_id;
552 int dp_clock;
553 int dp_lane_count;
554 bool tp3_supported;
555 u8 dpcd[DP_RECEIVER_CAP_SIZE];
556 u8 train_set[4];
557 u8 link_status[DP_LINK_STATUS_SIZE];
558 u8 tries;
559 bool use_dpencoder;
560 struct drm_dp_aux *aux;
561};
562
563static void radeon_dp_update_vs_emph(struct radeon_dp_link_train_info *dp_info)
564{
565 /* set the initial vs/emph on the source */
566 atombios_dig_transmitter_setup(dp_info->encoder,
567 ATOM_TRANSMITTER_ACTION_SETUP_VSEMPH,
568 0, dp_info->train_set[0]); /* sets all lanes at once */
569
570 /* set the vs/emph on the sink */
571 drm_dp_dpcd_write(dp_info->aux, DP_TRAINING_LANE0_SET,
572 dp_info->train_set, dp_info->dp_lane_count);
573}
574
575static void radeon_dp_set_tp(struct radeon_dp_link_train_info *dp_info, int tp)
576{
577 int rtp = 0;
578
579 /* set training pattern on the source */
580 if (ASIC_IS_DCE4(dp_info->rdev) || !dp_info->use_dpencoder) {
581 switch (tp) {
582 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_1:
583 rtp = ATOM_ENCODER_CMD_DP_LINK_TRAINING_PATTERN1;
584 break;
585 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_2:
586 rtp = ATOM_ENCODER_CMD_DP_LINK_TRAINING_PATTERN2;
587 break;
588 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_3:
589 rtp = ATOM_ENCODER_CMD_DP_LINK_TRAINING_PATTERN3;
590 break;
591 }
592 atombios_dig_encoder_setup(dp_info->encoder, rtp, 0);
593 } else {
594 switch (tp) {
595 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_1:
596 rtp = 0;
597 break;
598 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_2:
599 rtp = 1;
600 break;
601 }
602 radeon_dp_encoder_service(dp_info->rdev, ATOM_DP_ACTION_TRAINING_PATTERN_SEL,
603 dp_info->dp_clock, dp_info->enc_id, rtp);
604 }
605
606 /* enable training pattern on the sink */
607 drm_dp_dpcd_writeb(dp_info->aux, DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_SET, tp);
608}
609
610static int radeon_dp_link_train_init(struct radeon_dp_link_train_info *dp_info)
611{
612 struct radeon_encoder *radeon_encoder = to_radeon_encoder(dp_info->encoder);
613 struct radeon_encoder_atom_dig *dig = radeon_encoder->enc_priv;
614 u8 tmp;
615
616 /* power up the sink */
617 radeon_dp_set_rx_power_state(dp_info->connector, DP_SET_POWER_D0);
618
619 /* possibly enable downspread on the sink */
620 if (dp_info->dpcd[3] & 0x1)
621 drm_dp_dpcd_writeb(dp_info->aux,
622 DP_DOWNSPREAD_CTRL, DP_SPREAD_AMP_0_5);
623 else
624 drm_dp_dpcd_writeb(dp_info->aux,
625 DP_DOWNSPREAD_CTRL, 0);
626
627 if (dig->panel_mode == DP_PANEL_MODE_INTERNAL_DP2_MODE)
628 drm_dp_dpcd_writeb(dp_info->aux, DP_EDP_CONFIGURATION_SET, 1);
629
630 /* set the lane count on the sink */
631 tmp = dp_info->dp_lane_count;
632 if (drm_dp_enhanced_frame_cap(dp_info->dpcd))
633 tmp |= DP_LANE_COUNT_ENHANCED_FRAME_EN;
634 drm_dp_dpcd_writeb(dp_info->aux, DP_LANE_COUNT_SET, tmp);
635
636 /* set the link rate on the sink */
637 tmp = drm_dp_link_rate_to_bw_code(dp_info->dp_clock);
638 drm_dp_dpcd_writeb(dp_info->aux, DP_LINK_BW_SET, tmp);
639
640 /* start training on the source */
641 if (ASIC_IS_DCE4(dp_info->rdev) || !dp_info->use_dpencoder)
642 atombios_dig_encoder_setup(dp_info->encoder,
643 ATOM_ENCODER_CMD_DP_LINK_TRAINING_START, 0);
644 else
645 radeon_dp_encoder_service(dp_info->rdev, ATOM_DP_ACTION_TRAINING_START,
646 dp_info->dp_clock, dp_info->enc_id, 0);
647
648 /* disable the training pattern on the sink */
649 drm_dp_dpcd_writeb(dp_info->aux,
650 DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_SET,
651 DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_DISABLE);
652
653 return 0;
654}
655
656static int radeon_dp_link_train_finish(struct radeon_dp_link_train_info *dp_info)
657{
658 udelay(400);
659
660 /* disable the training pattern on the sink */
661 drm_dp_dpcd_writeb(dp_info->aux,
662 DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_SET,
663 DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_DISABLE);
664
665 /* disable the training pattern on the source */
666 if (ASIC_IS_DCE4(dp_info->rdev) || !dp_info->use_dpencoder)
667 atombios_dig_encoder_setup(dp_info->encoder,
668 ATOM_ENCODER_CMD_DP_LINK_TRAINING_COMPLETE, 0);
669 else
670 radeon_dp_encoder_service(dp_info->rdev, ATOM_DP_ACTION_TRAINING_COMPLETE,
671 dp_info->dp_clock, dp_info->enc_id, 0);
672
673 return 0;
674}
675
676static int radeon_dp_link_train_cr(struct radeon_dp_link_train_info *dp_info)
677{
678 bool clock_recovery;
679 u8 voltage;
680 int i;
681
682 radeon_dp_set_tp(dp_info, DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_1);
683 memset(dp_info->train_set, 0, 4);
684 radeon_dp_update_vs_emph(dp_info);
685
686 udelay(400);
687
688 /* clock recovery loop */
689 clock_recovery = false;
690 dp_info->tries = 0;
691 voltage = 0xff;
692 while (1) {
693 drm_dp_link_train_clock_recovery_delay(dp_info->dpcd);
694
695 if (drm_dp_dpcd_read_link_status(dp_info->aux,
696 dp_info->link_status) <= 0) {
697 DRM_ERROR("displayport link status failed\n");
698 break;
699 }
700
701 if (drm_dp_clock_recovery_ok(dp_info->link_status, dp_info->dp_lane_count)) {
702 clock_recovery = true;
703 break;
704 }
705
706 for (i = 0; i < dp_info->dp_lane_count; i++) {
707 if ((dp_info->train_set[i] & DP_TRAIN_MAX_SWING_REACHED) == 0)
708 break;
709 }
710 if (i == dp_info->dp_lane_count) {
711 DRM_ERROR("clock recovery reached max voltage\n");
712 break;
713 }
714
715 if ((dp_info->train_set[0] & DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_MASK) == voltage) {
716 ++dp_info->tries;
717 if (dp_info->tries == 5) {
718 DRM_ERROR("clock recovery tried 5 times\n");
719 break;
720 }
721 } else
722 dp_info->tries = 0;
723
724 voltage = dp_info->train_set[0] & DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_MASK;
725
726 /* Compute new train_set as requested by sink */
727 dp_get_adjust_train(dp_info->link_status, dp_info->dp_lane_count, dp_info->train_set);
728
729 radeon_dp_update_vs_emph(dp_info);
730 }
731 if (!clock_recovery) {
732 DRM_ERROR("clock recovery failed\n");
733 return -1;
734 } else {
735 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("clock recovery at voltage %d pre-emphasis %d\n",
736 dp_info->train_set[0] & DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_MASK,
737 (dp_info->train_set[0] & DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPHASIS_MASK) >>
738 DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPHASIS_SHIFT);
739 return 0;
740 }
741}
742
743static int radeon_dp_link_train_ce(struct radeon_dp_link_train_info *dp_info)
744{
745 bool channel_eq;
746
747 if (dp_info->tp3_supported)
748 radeon_dp_set_tp(dp_info, DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_3);
749 else
750 radeon_dp_set_tp(dp_info, DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_2);
751
752 /* channel equalization loop */
753 dp_info->tries = 0;
754 channel_eq = false;
755 while (1) {
756 drm_dp_link_train_channel_eq_delay(dp_info->dpcd);
757
758 if (drm_dp_dpcd_read_link_status(dp_info->aux,
759 dp_info->link_status) <= 0) {
760 DRM_ERROR("displayport link status failed\n");
761 break;
762 }
763
764 if (drm_dp_channel_eq_ok(dp_info->link_status, dp_info->dp_lane_count)) {
765 channel_eq = true;
766 break;
767 }
768
769 /* Try 5 times */
770 if (dp_info->tries > 5) {
771 DRM_ERROR("channel eq failed: 5 tries\n");
772 break;
773 }
774
775 /* Compute new train_set as requested by sink */
776 dp_get_adjust_train(dp_info->link_status, dp_info->dp_lane_count, dp_info->train_set);
777
778 radeon_dp_update_vs_emph(dp_info);
779 dp_info->tries++;
780 }
781
782 if (!channel_eq) {
783 DRM_ERROR("channel eq failed\n");
784 return -1;
785 } else {
786 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("channel eq at voltage %d pre-emphasis %d\n",
787 dp_info->train_set[0] & DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_MASK,
788 (dp_info->train_set[0] & DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPHASIS_MASK)
789 >> DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPHASIS_SHIFT);
790 return 0;
791 }
792}
793
794void radeon_dp_link_train(struct drm_encoder *encoder,
795 struct drm_connector *connector)
796{
797 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;
798 struct radeon_device *rdev = dev->dev_private;
799 struct radeon_encoder *radeon_encoder = to_radeon_encoder(encoder);
800 struct radeon_encoder_atom_dig *dig;
801 struct radeon_connector *radeon_connector;
802 struct radeon_connector_atom_dig *dig_connector;
803 struct radeon_dp_link_train_info dp_info;
804 int index;
805 u8 tmp, frev, crev;
806
807 if (!radeon_encoder->enc_priv)
808 return;
809 dig = radeon_encoder->enc_priv;
810
811 radeon_connector = to_radeon_connector(connector);
812 if (!radeon_connector->con_priv)
813 return;
814 dig_connector = radeon_connector->con_priv;
815
816 if ((dig_connector->dp_sink_type != CONNECTOR_OBJECT_ID_DISPLAYPORT) &&
817 (dig_connector->dp_sink_type != CONNECTOR_OBJECT_ID_eDP))
818 return;
819
820 /* DPEncoderService newer than 1.1 can't program properly the
821 * training pattern. When facing such version use the
822 * DIGXEncoderControl (X== 1 | 2)
823 */
824 dp_info.use_dpencoder = true;
825 index = GetIndexIntoMasterTable(COMMAND, DPEncoderService);
826 if (atom_parse_cmd_header(rdev->mode_info.atom_context, index, &frev, &crev)) {
827 if (crev > 1) {
828 dp_info.use_dpencoder = false;
829 }
830 }
831
832 dp_info.enc_id = 0;
833 if (dig->dig_encoder)
834 dp_info.enc_id |= ATOM_DP_CONFIG_DIG2_ENCODER;
835 else
836 dp_info.enc_id |= ATOM_DP_CONFIG_DIG1_ENCODER;
837 if (dig->linkb)
838 dp_info.enc_id |= ATOM_DP_CONFIG_LINK_B;
839 else
840 dp_info.enc_id |= ATOM_DP_CONFIG_LINK_A;
841
842 if (drm_dp_dpcd_readb(&radeon_connector->ddc_bus->aux, DP_MAX_LANE_COUNT, &tmp)
843 == 1) {
844 if (ASIC_IS_DCE5(rdev) && (tmp & DP_TPS3_SUPPORTED))
845 dp_info.tp3_supported = true;
846 else
847 dp_info.tp3_supported = false;
848 } else {
849 dp_info.tp3_supported = false;
850 }
851
852 memcpy(dp_info.dpcd, dig_connector->dpcd, DP_RECEIVER_CAP_SIZE);
853 dp_info.rdev = rdev;
854 dp_info.encoder = encoder;
855 dp_info.connector = connector;
856 dp_info.dp_lane_count = dig_connector->dp_lane_count;
857 dp_info.dp_clock = dig_connector->dp_clock;
858 dp_info.aux = &radeon_connector->ddc_bus->aux;
859
860 if (radeon_dp_link_train_init(&dp_info))
861 goto done;
862 if (radeon_dp_link_train_cr(&dp_info))
863 goto done;
864 if (radeon_dp_link_train_ce(&dp_info))
865 goto done;
866done:
867 if (radeon_dp_link_train_finish(&dp_info))
868 return;
869}
